ros2_control</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Factor-Robotics/odrive_ros2_control\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">119</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":119,\"repo\":\"Factor-Robotics/odrive_ros2_control\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - ODrive driver for ros2_control.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T10:15:30.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0037-build/\">The Unhandled Exception Podcast: Microsoft Build 2022</a> - May 25, 2022 - Microsoft have just had their annual Build conference - which comes with a whole host of exciting announcements and discussions about hot programming topics in the Microsoft developer space. And each year, I long for a podcast episode to come out straight after Build, overviewing them! Well, this year - this podcast aims to do just that! In this episode, I was joined by both Scott Hunter and Gaurav Seth to chat about various topics. Check out the links below for a guide to what we discussed. Duration: 71 minutes.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T08:42:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://herdingcode.com/herding-code-246-david-ortinau-on-net-maui/\">David Ortinau on .NET MAUI</a> - May 27, 2022 - Jon Galloway talks to David Ortinau about <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/maui/what-is-maui\">.NET MAUI</a>. Duration: 41 minutes. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OyqzWAivI7I\">YouTube video</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T08:40:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mybuild.microsoft.com/en-US/sessions/ddf48da7-d3e6-4ba5-affd-b5735ce205fa?source=sessions\">Future Possibilities for .NET Core and WASI (WebAssembly on the Server)</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-28%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=microsoft\" alt=\"duration\"> May 25, 2022 - WebAssembly is moving beyond the browser and is pitched to become a foundational element of modern cloud-native architecture. It lets any language compile to universal binaries that run on any OS or processor, robustly sandboxed and with great performance. This session covers a new approach to running .NET in WASI environments. You’ll see how your existing .NET code could be built into WASI-compliant modules, plus the opportunities this opens. This is experimental, not yet a committed product.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T08:36:49.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aorumbayev/awesome-algorand","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2><h3>Projects</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://forum.ax/\">FORUM</a> - A proof-of-stake social network on the Algorand blockchain.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T08:11:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M4tgU-V7peI\">Revisiting MVVM</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-20%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> April 21, 2022 - Carl revisits the topic of MVVM with Blazor, clarifying your options.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T07:56:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5q21Olur050\">Queryable Repositories</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-28%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> April 14, 2022 - Build a generic repository that the client can query.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T07:56:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vn6dKN_hTrs\">Managing App State with Fluxor</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-23%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> March 31, 2022 - pp State Management using Fluxor, a Flux/Redux library for Blazor.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T07:56:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Components &#x26; Libraries</h2><h4>Table</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/HC200ok/vue3-easy-data-table\">vue3-easy-data-table</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/HC200ok/vue3-easy-data-table\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">163</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":163,\"repo\":\"HC200ok/vue3-easy-data-table\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A easy-to-use data table component made with Vue.js 3.x, referring to the API and UI of data table component in Vuetify 2.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T07:55:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mybuild.microsoft.com/en-US/sessions/599c82b6-0c5a-4add-9961-48b85d9ffde0\">Build native apps for any device with .NET and Visual Studio</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-51%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=microsoft\" alt=\"duration\"> May 25, 2022 - See how you can quickly and iteratively build modern, native and hybrid web apps for any device with Visual Studio and .NET Multi-platform App UI (.NET MAUI). We’ll take you on a tour of the tools and frameworks that can speed up your development time to create powerful, native desktop and mobile apps for Windows, macOS, iOS, and Android from a single codebase with .NET MAUI. We’ll also show you how to enhance your Blazor web apps with native device capabilities.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T07:43:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ripienaar/free-for-dev","categoryHTML":"<h2>Flutter Related and Building IOS Apps without Mac</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://flutlab.io/\">FlutLab</a> - FlutLab is a modern Flutter online IDE and the best place to create, debug, and build cross-platform projects. Build iOS (Without Mac) and Android apps with Flutter.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T05:42:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ripienaar/free-for-dev","categoryHTML":"<h2>Flutter Related and Building IOS Apps without Mac</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codemagic.io/\">CodeMagic</a> - Codemagic is a fully hosted and managed CI/CD for mobile apps. You can build, test, deploy with a GUI based CI/CD tool. Free tier offers 500 free minutes/month, and Mac Mini instance with 2.3Ghz and 8gb of RAM.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-27T05:42:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ripienaar/free-for-dev","categoryHTML":"<h2>Flutter Related and Building IOS Apps without Mac</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://flutterflow.io/\">FlutterFlow</a> -  FlutterFlow is a browser-based drag-and-drop interface to build mobile app using flutter.</li>","updatedAt":"20